qas.question: What Schwarzenegger film was 1991's highest-grossing movie?
What organization named Schwarzenegger the "International Star of the Decade" in 1993?

answers.text: the National Association of Theatre Owners

qas.question: What 1994 film brought Schwarzenegger back together with director James Cameron?

context: Schwarzenegger's commercial peak was his return as the title character in 1991's <a0_0>Terminator 2: Judgment Day<a0_0/>, which was the highest-grossing film of 1991. In 1993, <a1_0>the National Association of Theatre Owners<a1_0/> named him the "International Star of the Decade". His next film project, the 1993 self-aware action comedy spoof Last Action Hero, was released opposite Jurassic Park, and did not do well at the box office. His next film, the comedy drama <a2_0>True Lies<a2_0/> (1994), was a popular spy film, and saw Schwarzenegger reunited with James Cameron.
